<asp:Content ID="Content3" ContentPlaceHolderID="Head" runat="server">
    <%= Html.Title("Privacy") %>
</asp:Content>

<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="Body" runat="server">
    <div class="info privacy">
        <h1>InsideWord Privacy Notice</h1>
        <div class="h1hr"></div>
        <br />
        <p><i>Updated as of June 13, 2010</i></p>
        <dl>
            <dt>Personal Information</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Browsing <i>InsideWord</i>: </b>You can read articles on <i>InsideWord</i> without having an
                        <i>InsideWord</i> Account. You also can contact us by emailing us directly without having
                        to register for an account. </li>
                    <li><b>Your <i>InsideWord</i> Account: </b>For some activities on <i>InsideWord</i>, like publishing
                        articles, voting, posting comments, and flagging articles, you need an <i>InsideWord</i>
                        Account. We ask for some personal information when you create an account, including
                        your email address and a password, which is used to protect your account from unauthorized
                        access. </li>
                    <li><b>Usage Information: </b>When you use <i>InsideWord</i>, we may record information about
                        your usage of the site, such as the articles you select, votes, the frequency and
                        size of data transfers, and information you display about yourself as well as information
                        you click on in <i>InsideWord</i> (including UI elements, settings). If you are logged
                        in, we may associate that information with your <i>InsideWord</i> Account. </li>
                    <li><b>Content Uploaded to Site: </b>Any personal information or content that you voluntarily
                        disclose online (e.g., comments, articles, your profile page) may be collected and
                        used by others. </li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
            <dt>Uses</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li>If you submit personal information to <i>InsideWord</i>, we may use that information to
                        operate, maintain, and improve the features and functionality of <i>InsideWord</i>, and
                        to process any flagging activity or other communication you send to us. </li>
                    <li>We do not use your email address or other personal information to send commercial
                        or marketing messages without your consent. We may use your email address without
                        further consent for non-marketing or administrative purposes (such as notifying
                        you of major <i>InsideWord</i> changes or for customer service purposes). </li>
                    <li>We use cookies, web beacons, and log file information to: (a) store information
                        so that you will not have to re-enter it during your visit or the next time you
                        visit <i>InsideWord</i>; (b) provide custom, personalized content and information; (c)
                        monitor the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns; (d) monitor aggregate metrics
                        such as total number of visitors and pages viewed; and (e) track your entries, submissions,
                        and status in promotions, sweepstakes, and contests. </li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
            <dt>Information That is Publicly Available</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li>When you create an <i>InsideWord</i> Account, some information about your <i>InsideWord</i> Account
                        and your account activity will be provided to other users of <i>InsideWord</i>. </li>
                    <li>Your <i>InsideWord</i> Account name, not your email address, is displayed to other users
                        when you engage in certain activities on <i>InsideWord</i>, such as when you upload articles
                        or send messages through <i>InsideWord</i>. Other users can contact you by leaving a message
                        or comment on the site. </li>
                    <li>Any articles that you submit to <i>InsideWord</i> may be redistributed through the internet
                        and other media channels, and may be viewed by other <i>InsideWord</i> users or the general
                        public. </li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
        </dl>
        <dl>
            <dt>Your Choices</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li>You may, of course, decline to submit personal information through <i>InsideWord</i>, in
                        which case you can still view articles and explore <i>InsideWord</i>, but <i>InsideWord</i> may
                        not be able to provide certain services to you. </li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
        </dl>
    </div>
</asp:Content>

